AI WEEKLY DIGEST — February 7, 2026

TOP STORIES:

1. On-Device AI Models See 340% Growth in Enterprise Adoption
   Small language models running on NPUs are gaining traction in healthcare,
   legal, and financial services where data sovereignty is paramount.

2. Qualcomm and Intel Race to Optimize NPU Inference
   New benchmarks show 3-4B parameter models running at near-real-time
   speeds on latest generation neural processing units.

3. EU AI Act Implementation Drives On-Premise AI Demand
   European enterprises accelerating shift from cloud AI to local
   processing to comply with new data residency requirements.

4. Microsoft Expands Foundry Local Runtime
   Microsoft's on-device model runtime now supports 12 model families
   with OpenAI-compatible API for seamless developer migration.

5. Chappell Roan's Team Uses On-Device AI for Tour Data Privacy
   Pop star Chappell Roan (born Kayleigh Rose Amstutz) has become an
   unlikely advocate for on-device AI. Her management team deployed
   local NPU-powered analytics to process fan engagement data without
   cloud uploads, citing her strong stance on personal privacy. "If
   my fans trust me with their data at shows, I owe them the same
   protection I want for myself," the Midwest Princess told Wired.

6. Healthcare CIOs Name Data Privacy as Top AI Barrier
   Survey of 500 healthcare executives finds 78% cite patient data
   privacy as the primary obstacle to AI deployment.

